p: \bGet lost. We're busy. Don't make me want to kill you more than I already do.

\bWe don't want money, power, fame, or even legendary Pokemon.
\bA truly perfect Pokemon. One that is undefeatable, inconquerable.\nOne with no counters, and no move or strategy can stop.
\bWe've been searching for this in everything we've done.\nFor example, Delta Pokemon- we thought certain Pokemon might be stronger with different types,
\bIn the Kalos Region, a new battle technique was discovered.\nIt's become common practice now, but how it works is still a mystery to scientists today.
\bThis is called Mega Evolution.\nWe need to understand it completely.
\bTaen has a Pokemon with a Mega Stone on his team right now.
\bWe want data. If you battle against Taen, we can analyze how well his Mega Evolution does in battle and how it can be improved.
\bFight Taen, and we'll let you pass through.\nYou're right, you can get into the Jade Tower from here.

\rI'm going to fix him, and then I'm coming for you.
\bI couldn't care less about you, kiddo.
\bI have information that could help both of you.
\bIt'll help you find your friend and get up the mountain.
\bI don't want much in return, just two small favors.
\bI want your time to test something, once again.
\b...and, just a tiny bit of Mew's DNA.
\bI have data on all your battles. I know you battled it recently- you're probably covered in it.
\rWhat? Why would you need Mew's DNA?
\bIt's my schtick, kid. I make Pokemon, experimental versions of them, anyways.
\bAre you really so stupid you can't think of a single reason wh- nevermind.
\bIt doesn't matter. What do you say?
\bI've got information. I need your time and Mew's DNA.
\bHmph. Well, fine. I'll still be here. Don't really know how you plan to get up the mountain.
\bI'm glad we could come to an agreement.
\bAh, a skin flake, this will do fine.
\rI really wish you didn't do that, \pn.
\rI don't know what he plans to do with that... no matter how obvious it is to him.
\bYou seemed like the smartest one in the special snowflake club.
\bNo possible clue as to what I'm trying to create?
\bTaen, the machine deposits it directly into the Master Ball, yes?
Taen: \bThis is revenge for the embarrassment you two caused me earlier.
\bWe've tried so many plans in our pursuit of perfection.
\bA perfect Pokemon... we've tried so many modifications and strategies.
\bWe've changed their types. Made Mega Stones. Gave them suits of armor.
\bWe've even tried fusing them together to create the perfect legendary.
\b...but we've never tried creating one from scratch.
\bCome out! Mewtwo! Emerge and serve me!
\bYou've had Kyurem, Mewtwo... even the entire Tao trio, and you still couldn't take them down.
\bAt this moment, Zenith is the most powerful human being alive.
\bHe has some sort of ability that lets him take control of others- using a Psychic-type Pokemon, maybe.
\bI know that the hard way. He took the shard of the crystal we found.
\bOne of our scientists was a double-agent for him.
\bNone of us have any clue where this power comes from. No Psychic-type I know can control people on this level... and now that he has a piece of the crystal, I
don't know how far his power can extend.
\bThe virus I created extends life by strengthening the body and its resistance.
\bThis improved immune system seems to let the\nvictim actually... ignore Zenith's power.
\bHowever, the vaccine doesn't do anything.\nI've stolen it, and studied it. It's a complete dud.
\bI have a hunch his control booths and checkpoints have something to do with his ability.
\bSo, Harmony's father or your friend should be able to get you up the mountain.
\bI've been tracking their location. I can-
\rYou know where they are?! You didn't tell us?
\bI can only read the psychic signals emitted when they use their abilities.\nThey have the same signature as Deoxys, and I'm sure there's no Deoxys around here.
\bI've met with them, and negotiated with them.
\bI've agreed to not disclose their location and allow them to continue whatever it is they're doing- so long as they do me small favors from time to time.
\bI've asked them to meet you at Mount Rose.
\bYou can talk to them. Negotiate with them. Do whatever it is you need to do.
\bI don't want to talk to you two anymore. They're waiting for you.
\rI... I don't like this, \pn. I'll meet you up the mountain. If Damian is actually there...
\rUnless... do you want to come with me? Or do you want to make your way back?
\rLet's see if Damian really... really is there.
\bGet outta here. They won't wait forever.

\bMetchi Town lab in shambles due to second Volcarona. Evidence suggests a lethal toxin emitted into the air upon evolution.
\bI have begun to move all my equipment to my alternate base beneath Helios City. It's not the same, but it'll do.
\bAfter the toxin has cleared, I will make a note to return to retrieve what remains.
\bThe potential of this Pokemon is astounding, however, I need to find a way to control it.
\bPerhaps a legendary Pokemon of some sort? I've instructed Taen to begin a search forthe Unovan dragons.
\bAs the legendary Pokemon that represents perfection,  the Original Dragon should almost definitely be able to deal with my little Volcarona problem.
Huh, there was a key of some sort in the back of the book.

\bI've been continuing research on restraining disobedient Pokemon, and I've come across a patent filed by Anastasia for the creation of protecting and controlling
\bThis is fantastic news. Not only would armor help me control Delta Volcarona, I can add it to the list of possible ways a perfect Pokemon might be created.
\bIt's definitely worth looking into, for multiple reasons.
\bTaen seems to have had some success with the Unovan dragons task, having found Kyurem and Zekrom already.
\bI will ask him to commission an armor for Zekrom off of Anatasia. Perhaps that would be enough to make Zekrom perfect- but I'd also like to reverse engineer it
myself create an armor for Delta Volcarona.
\bThis should keep it docile enough to bend to my will.

\bSuccess! The armor was capable in restricting and controlling Delta Volcarona.
\bI've left a prototype here just in case something happens, but everything seems to be going well so far.
\bInterestingly, while doing research into armor, I've found some of the old Team Rocket files.
\bApparently, they also attempted to use armor to control a disobedient, powerful Pokemon- Mewtwo.
\bConveniently enough, the files contained a blueprint for the cloning machine they used to make it.
\bIf I have time, I'll see if I can make it myself. I'd love to have a Mewtwo under my command.

\bWhile doing research into cloning and DNA (for the Mewtwo cloning machine I've been developing), I've found links to a very interesting event that happened in
\bSomething called the Delta Episode: where a battle between Deoxys and Rayquaza caused many small DNA changes throughout the region.
\bHarmony and her father are from Hoenn- this definitely bears investigating.
\bI'm also interested in the impacts this may have had on Mega Evolution.
\bRayquaza seems to be the original Mega... and it was Mega Evolution that seems to have triggered the whole event.
\bThere seems to be some stuff about an ancient king and a meteorite being the origin of Mega Stones.
\bIt's a long shot, but perhaps... some stones could be created for some of the Deltas I've been experimenting on?

\bI've been having trouble with the whole Delta Mega Evolution idea I had a while back.
\bIt seems there's more to Mega Evolution than just the stone.
\bA Pokemon needs a strong bond of trust and love between itself and its trainer.
\bWhile there's a low chance of that ever applying to me... perhaps...
\bMy old college friend, Vanessa Sylvan, ended up being a professor.
\bIt's her job to give Pokemon to kids, who are of course, naturally trusting and loving.
\bI'll give her some of my spare experimental Pokemon. Test subjects, disguised as failures.
\bI have a modified Mega Ring that records data and sends it to my servers. If these Pokemon ever find a strong connection, I'll get in contact with the trainers and
\bI hope Sylvan takes them- a better understanding of Mega Evolution could be very useful.
